The detailed electrochemical characterization of the herein
utilized ZFO-based anodes was already reported previously.
Such electrodes showed a remarkable rate performance and
cycling stability. Being speciﬁ cally interesting for the applica-
tion of these electrodes in a lithium-ion full-cell, however, the
irreversible charge consumption within the ﬁ rst cycle was
slightly less than 30%. This initial irreversible capacity was
mainly attributed to the formation of a solid electrolyte inter-
phase (SEI) layer on the active material particles surface. Nev-
